WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.937 --> 00:00:02.549
Good evening, family.

00:00:02.549 --> 00:00:05.942
Thank you for joining us again tonight.

00:00:05.942 --> 00:00:09.660
It's Diana and Brandon, and we're excited to be here.

00:00:09.660 --> 00:00:15.519
We have some things in our heart, but I don't have a lot; I'm just going to pray with you all.

00:00:19.107 --> 00:00:21.813
I know we came on a little bit later than normal.

00:00:22.586 --> 00:00:28.750
I try to come on by then, but as you're driving around like we were today, we could feel the presence.

00:00:28.750 --> 00:00:31.690
I told Diana, 'Don't you just feel the presence of the Lord so strongly?

00:00:31.690 --> 00:00:32.559
' And she could, too.

00:00:32.779 --> 00:00:40.960
It was right after we watched Billy Burke last night; the presence of the Lord was tangible when he was in Orlando.

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:54.628
Truly, I have never experienced through a phone or a device watching and feeling the presence of the Lord fill your car or your house like that.

00:00:56.045 --> 00:01:02.640
It lingered all night and all day.

00:01:02.898 --> 00:01:14.210
As I was seeking Him and as I went to the prayer group last night, I had an open-eyed vision of Jesus.

00:01:17.973 --> 00:01:23.656
He came, and I didn't know that Diana had been praying for me that afternoon.

00:01:26.409 --> 00:01:34.560
After I told her what happened, she started crying and said, 'Brandon, I was interceding for you, just asking God to give you a refreshing.

00:01:34.969 --> 00:01:38.430
I know you pour out so much and you're tired a lot.

00:01:38.430 --> 00:01:45.732
' She said, 'I was in my own private prayer time this morning, and I was praying for you.

00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:51.240
I asked the Lord to become real to Braden even more, help him, and give him strength.

00:01:51.240 --> 00:02:01.504
' When I went to prayer that night—which was Sunday night, I guess—my life just runs together.

00:02:05.646 --> 00:02:10.960
Last night, He spoke to me, and I said, 'Lord, I miss You.

00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:18.080
' All of a sudden, I just closed my eyes, and Jesus appeared before me in a vision, like He does whenever I'm on here.

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:26.662
He started talking to me about some things that were very private, encouraging me just like she was asking.

00:02:27.005 --> 00:02:32.560
Because of all the things that I had delivered this last week, it was hard.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:35.013
I said, 'Lord, I need refreshing.

00:02:35.013 --> 00:02:36.373
Is everything okay?

00:02:36.373 --> 00:02:39.920
Are we cool right now?

00:02:39.920 --> 00:02:44.080
' And He said, 'Well, why wouldn't it be?

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:47.459
' I said, 'Well, I've had a rough week.

00:02:47.459 --> 00:02:50.879
' And He said, 'Brandon, you just need to be refreshed.

00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:52.012
You're dry.

00:02:52.012 --> 00:02:55.589
You're thirsty.

00:02:55.599 --> 00:03:16.400
' You know, ladies and gentlemen, when you are so used to going through the valley of life, He said, 'Once you pass a certain test—Jesus said this to me yesterday—once you pass a certain test in school, you don't keep going there.

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:18.319
You graduate.

00:03:18.319 --> 00:03:31.120
' As you are in the body of Christ, as you are on the potter's wheel and as you go from glory to glory, you don't camp in the valley.

00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:37.165
You don't camp in what you're going through for the refining fire.

00:03:37.165 --> 00:03:47.360
The refining fire is for a season, and once you pass the test, you don't have to take it again.

00:03:47.588 --> 00:03:55.519
He said, 'Brandon, you went through those things and you passed those tests, but you're so used to camping around what you had been through in the past.

00:03:55.519 --> 00:04:09.475
' From working at my grandmother's, working at the church, and having Megan, you build a wall of defense where you're always looking for the next blow.

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:21.099
You feel that victim mentality where you walk through life feeling like you're always going through something because you're growing from glory to glory.

00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:35.170
But those tests were for that season of life.

00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:50.400
The Lord says as you grow and mature, those things become the tests that you passed.

00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:55.460
Just like in fifth, sixth, or seventh grade, you don't go back and repeat those.

00:04:55.460 --> 00:05:01.429
You just take what you learned and add to it.

00:05:05.100 --> 00:05:05.360
You keep going until you graduate.

00:05:06.296 --> 00:05:15.547
You always remember what you learned, but you never have to take the test that you took to get to the next level.

00:05:15.547 --> 00:05:17.911
You go from glory to glory.

00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:32.560
That's what He was showing me: that season is done, and He is taking me somewhere new.

00:05:32.880 --> 00:05:39.147
There are seasons of blessing and refreshing in every believer's life.

00:05:39.147 --> 00:05:43.120
It's not always about the valley.

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:50.400
We go through hard times in our Christian walk, and that's what makes us stronger.

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:57.520
Diana found this man who had died and went to heaven.

00:06:03.600 --> 00:06:14.000
In his testimony, he came back and said his mother told him in heaven, 'Don't forget what pain feels like, because you won't have any of it up here.

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:17.759
' Don't take it for granted.

00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:24.240
Pain causes you to grow; trials cause you to grow.

00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:32.160
There are no trials up there to spur you to grow.

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:35.520
The hard times are what refines you.

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:43.851
A lot of times, when your flesh is screaming the loudest is when God has His hand on that potter's wheel and He's pushing down.

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:51.640
Does God cause the pain?

00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:52.100
No.

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:56.230
I want to tell you God is a rewarder of those who diligently seek Him.

00:06:56.230 --> 00:06:59.440
He is a blesser, not a curser.

00:06:59.440 --> 00:07:04.880
But because we live in a fallen world, hard times come.

00:07:06.205 --> 00:07:11.770
I always stay on God's side; God does not put sickness on people to teach them a lesson.

00:07:14.446 --> 00:07:15.680
I don't believe that.

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:18.992
There's no sickness in heaven, so how can He give it to you?

00:07:19.264 --> 00:07:28.731
When you get to heaven, He doesn't have any sickness there, and He and the devil aren't buddies joining up to inflict His kids.

00:07:28.731 --> 00:07:32.560
What kind of father would do that?

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:42.548
The Bible says, 'If you, being evil, give good gifts to your children, how much more does your heavenly Father give good gifts to those that love Him?

00:07:42.548 --> 00:07:47.589
' He's not giving snakes or sickness to teach you something.

00:07:57.620 --> 00:08:13.840
Because we live in a fallen world and go through life, it molds us and you grow—and also because of our own dumb decisions.

00:08:16.729 --> 00:08:21.538
But regarding the valley, the man said, 'Don't forget the way pain feels because you won't feel any in heaven.

00:08:21.538 --> 00:08:26.079
' The trial makes you grow.

00:08:26.079 --> 00:08:33.680
She said, 'And don't forget what touch feels like in this way, because it's different in heaven.

00:08:33.680 --> 00:08:44.834
' When he went to heaven—and I know he had an authentic encounter, this man wept the whole time—the glory of the Lord was present.

00:08:53.830 --> 00:09:01.759
He was a druggie and had a massive heart attack, and when he went up there, he had all this about the Father and all the inadequacies that we feel because God is so perfect.

00:09:04.959 --> 00:09:10.560
But every single thing he said was things that Jesus had said to me.

00:09:22.480 --> 00:09:22.731
Every single thing, not every single thing, but a lot of them.

00:09:30.113 --> 00:09:34.240
I don't, because that's exaggeration.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:45.977
Some of the things he said the Lord said to him were what the Lord said to me privately in the visitations I've had with him, and I thought, he said that to him too?

00:09:45.977 --> 00:09:50.540
Isn't that amazing that he'll help you through it?

00:09:50.540 --> 00:09:53.760
That you can't mess your life up?

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.529
The footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:09:56.529 --> 00:09:57.943
Brandon, he said that to me.

00:09:57.943 --> 00:10:00.419
The footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:10:00.419 --> 00:10:08.605
No matter how hard you try, you couldn't mess your life up if you're seeking me and you're looking towards my face.

00:10:08.605 --> 00:10:18.399
He said, You can't mess your life up because I'll turn what the devil meant for bad and turn it around for good for you, Brandon, if you're always looking for me.

00:10:18.399 --> 00:10:27.860
No matter how bad you mess your life up, how bad you might think you've messed your life up, if you're seeking the Lord, he'll turn it on a dime.

00:10:27.860 --> 00:10:29.966
It's about putting Jesus first.

00:10:29.966 --> 00:10:33.920
We must learn to put Jesus first.

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:37.304
He is everything.

00:10:37.680 --> 00:10:52.079
If you put him first in your marriage, if you put him first with your children, if you put him first in your finances—that's why the Bible says, you know, a lot of people get all upset when you tell them about tithing and giving, but we were forced to learn how to tithe.

00:10:52.079 --> 00:10:53.640
Our church forced us to tithe.

00:10:54.823 --> 00:10:58.329
Because we were on staff, if we didn't tithe, they'd fire you.

00:10:58.329 --> 00:11:08.959
And so I knew whenever you're forced to learn how to tithe, it then becomes habit because we worked there for so many years.

00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:11.332
So people say, Oh, I don't believe in tithing.

00:11:11.332 --> 00:11:14.320
Oh, I believe with all my heart.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:23.947
I believe in tithing more than—I'm telling you, I have got the revelation of tithing, not because of something that I wanted, but because I was forced to.

00:11:23.947 --> 00:11:26.250
And I thank God for Mark all the time.

00:11:26.250 --> 00:11:31.160
Pastor Mark, he taught us the fundamentals of tithing.

00:11:31.573 --> 00:11:40.720
It was, like I said, strong-armed, but I'm thankful that he did it because if he wouldn't have done it, I wouldn't have got the revelation of it.

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:41.742
I was a tipper.

00:11:41.742 --> 00:11:42.951
I was a tipper.

00:11:44.160 --> 00:11:52.800
I'd give God a little bit here and there, and you give him what you could or whatever, whenever it was convenient.

00:11:52.800 --> 00:12:02.320
But as we grew and God started speaking to Diana, she got her education, her master's degree, and did all that through her schooling and pushing as hard as we did.

00:12:05.867 --> 00:12:10.080
But then the Lord gave us an idea outside of what we naturally would have thought.

00:12:10.240 --> 00:12:12.160
It was Diana that had the revelation.

00:12:12.160 --> 00:12:16.880
It's amazing how many times the Lord has used her to help our family.

00:12:17.627 --> 00:12:19.607
Husbands, listen to your wives.

00:12:19.607 --> 00:12:24.560
They have wisdom, and wives, listen to your husbands.

00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:31.200
But I'm just saying don't always just think that you have it all and that you know God, well, I'm the head of the house and you better listen to me.

00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:37.279
I thank God that she had the idea for eBay and Poshmark.

00:12:37.279 --> 00:12:40.960
Thank God it came from a Holy Ghost-inspired idea of desperation.

00:12:40.960 --> 00:12:43.839
Couldn't pay our electric bill.

00:12:43.839 --> 00:12:53.639
But I'm saying as we tithed and we gave, we kept tithing and we keep giving, and it's become foundation in our life where God is always first.

00:12:53.639 --> 00:12:56.140
That was where I was going with that.

00:12:56.140 --> 00:13:06.700
By keeping God first in your marriage, praying together, reading the Bible together, reading little books like this together, we keep our marriage fresh that way.

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:12.320
And I don't always say there haven't been hard days; we go through it.

00:13:12.320 --> 00:13:20.320
But we know if we pray together, we stay together, and we take communion together, and we know that if we seek him together, we'll find him.

00:13:24.631 --> 00:13:28.364
I've learned to lean on her discernment a lot.

00:13:28.969 --> 00:13:32.171
I believe there's a lot of discernment in women.

00:13:32.171 --> 00:13:35.147
God has gifted women with great discernment.

00:13:35.147 --> 00:13:36.267
Don't you agree?

00:13:36.267 --> 00:13:40.480
They're like, it's like Billy Burke says, they're the rear guard of the household.

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:43.559
They're able to see things a lot of times that the man doesn't see.

00:13:43.559 --> 00:13:52.329
And when she gets these emails and people are always saying they've got something going on and Diana says, I have to check.

00:13:52.329 --> 00:13:54.183
I have to pray about that.

00:13:54.183 --> 00:13:55.897
Let's pray about that together more.

00:13:55.897 --> 00:13:57.769
And I say, You see something I don't see.

00:13:59.227 --> 00:13:59.591
Okay.

00:13:59.591 --> 00:14:01.060
Well, I trust it.

00:14:01.060 --> 00:14:05.120
And she says, I don't always trust the motive behind the individual.

00:14:05.120 --> 00:14:06.507
You have to pray.

00:14:06.507 --> 00:14:13.420
And we learn as you intercede and as you pray and you grow, God will develop you and you'll go from glory to glory.

00:14:14.180 --> 00:14:28.560
But I was praying over things today and the anointing and the presence of the Lord was so strong, and he was talking to me about what's about to happen.

00:14:29.893 --> 00:14:36.942
Going and praying into 2026, this is a year you can't just let your guard down.

00:14:36.942 --> 00:14:39.920
You must be spiritually alert.

00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:44.000
2026 is going to be a high alert year.

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:48.800
We must pray for our country concerning terrorist attacks, Red Dawn experiences.

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:56.571
Oh, Brandon, you said—I'm telling you by the spirit of God, you must have your eyes open.

00:14:56.571 --> 00:15:14.330
Do not become dazed for the days that are ahead concerning this nation, concerning our president, his safety, and all the things that I keep telling you and talking to you all about.

00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:18.453
This is a time to have your senses heightened all around the world.

00:15:18.453 --> 00:15:20.171
You say, Well, I'm not in America.

00:15:20.171 --> 00:15:30.190
Well, if you live in Australia, if you live in Europe, if you have your spiritual discernment heightened by praying and fasting, by seeking him, you will find him.

00:15:32.116 --> 00:15:34.731
This is a time not for the church to be asleep.

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:37.760
You must wake up.

00:15:38.059 --> 00:15:45.839
I'm telling you, closing out 2025 and really coming alive in 2026 even more.

00:15:45.839 --> 00:15:50.720
You need to have your eyes open.

00:15:50.720 --> 00:16:12.389
I have a great warning going into the future and praying over this year, praying over 2026, but I was seeing the old generals and he said, Go back to the wells, the wells of the revival.

00:16:12.389 --> 00:16:16.480
You see the picture behind us?

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:30.580
That Thanksgiving picture was what I saw in the spirit when the Pilgrims came and they put their hands together and they made a covenant to God at Plymouth Rock.

00:16:30.580 --> 00:16:47.622
And I saw an actual rock that they stood around and they prayed and they took communion and they dedicated the land of America as one nation that they would have a God-fearing—they dedicated this land, this property where we are.

00:16:47.622 --> 00:17:05.510
We dedicate this land to Jesus that we will be a people that live by faith, that have a freedom of religion and all the things that they sought out for.

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:13.691
The Lord said to me, he said, Brandon—he brought it up to me tonight, Brandon—those prayers still go before me.

00:17:13.691 --> 00:17:20.400
The prayers of your founding fathers clear back at Plymouth Rock.

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:22.640
They go before me.

00:17:22.640 --> 00:17:35.737
George Washington's prayers on the battlefield when he was fighting the British, when he was fighting the battle and he was weary, and I gave him supernatural strength to fight for the land.

00:17:35.737 --> 00:17:40.220
When George Washington had bullets flying all around him, they said bullets were all in his cloak.

00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:49.440
His jacket, what he had on, all those bullets from—he had bullets all through his clothes because they were that close to hitting him.

00:17:49.440 --> 00:17:53.760
But the hand of the Lord was on him to protect him for this nation.

00:17:53.760 --> 00:18:12.080
And as he was praying, God, give me strength to finish this battle, God supernaturally gave him a strength, knowing that there was going to be a Diana and a Brandon standing here today praying for you in America saying Jesus is coming.

00:18:12.080 --> 00:18:12.410
Jesus is coming.

00:18:13.070 --> 00:18:14.720
Do you know our friend?

00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:18.857
We had over 100 people get saved this last video.

00:18:19.131 --> 00:18:21.591
That's what it's all about to us.

00:18:21.973 --> 00:18:31.778
97, Braden said so far just on the livestream, and then how many people on emails and everything else, has been over the top from the other videos.

00:18:31.778 --> 00:18:44.587
But as I saw in the spirit George Washington fighting the battle and God gave him strength and he prayed that this nation would be a nation that feared God.

00:18:44.587 --> 00:18:49.679
Those prayers still go before the Father.

00:18:49.679 --> 00:18:50.560
He's not forgotten it.

00:18:50.560 --> 00:18:54.639
And he said to me, "You will not be a goat nation.

00:18:54.639 --> 00:18:56.340
You will be a sheep nation.

00:18:56.340 --> 00:18:59.315
" And a great shaking to awaken is coming to this land.

00:18:59.590 --> 00:19:10.240
It will not be a land that turns its back and does things against me, becoming a goat nation from the Father.

00:19:10.240 --> 00:19:14.400
We will remain a sheep nation.

00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:17.280
I want to be a sheep; I don't want to be a goat.

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:24.480
So I want to encourage you all today: America is not done for.

00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:26.479
America is not falling off.

00:19:26.479 --> 00:19:35.005
Well, we see Mamdani, or whatever his name is, up there in New York and all these things—yeah, there are some radical things happening right now.

00:19:36.608 --> 00:19:55.280
Braden had a list of all the churches in the last 24 months in Texas alone; 48 mosques were raised up in Texas in this area right here in the last 24 months.

00:19:55.280 --> 00:20:02.750
48 mosques were created or raised up in Texas.

00:20:12.053 --> 00:20:15.850
Ladies and gentlemen, does anybody know this stuff is going on?

00:20:15.850 --> 00:20:25.418
As we see this stuff happen, a great shaking is coming.

00:20:26.029 --> 00:20:31.080
Go back to what he said: go back to the family units.

00:20:31.080 --> 00:20:34.000
Go back to the foundation.

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:36.960
Go back to the basics, the ABCs.

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:42.799
Don't get out of the ABCs.

00:20:42.799 --> 00:20:48.960
There are so many people that have forgotten the ABCs.

00:20:54.057 --> 00:20:54.274
What does that mean?

00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:09.440
The fundamentals of Christianity.

00:21:09.440 --> 00:21:17.680
It all ties together, what he's telling me and what I'm trying to tell y'all tonight.

00:21:17.680 --> 00:21:23.690
Don't forget kindergarten; don't forget it because you're going to use what you learned in first grade.

00:21:23.690 --> 00:21:26.190
It all goes from glory to glory.

00:21:26.190 --> 00:21:33.093
It's the same way with your faith and your walk with the Father.

00:21:36.697 --> 00:21:36.960
You learn your confession.

00:21:37.946 --> 00:21:46.027
You learn how to speak things and call those things that be not as though they were in Romans.

00:21:46.027 --> 00:21:51.840
You've got to learn that life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:56.640
The more you speak out of your mouth, what you're saying is what you're living.

00:21:56.640 --> 00:22:01.147
What you said yesterday is what you'll live tomorrow.

00:22:01.147 --> 00:22:05.554
What you're living today is what you said yesterday.

00:22:07.440 --> 00:22:09.307
You must understand that life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:22:09.307 --> 00:22:10.649
Most people just say things flippantly.

00:22:10.649 --> 00:22:19.220
Even Pastor Chip and Candace say all the time, "What's the first thing that comes out of your mouth?

00:22:19.220 --> 00:22:21.440
What's your first response?

00:22:21.440 --> 00:22:27.679
" What's your first response to the circumstance when the doctor gives you a bad report?

00:22:27.679 --> 00:22:30.263
"Well, your blood pressure is too high.

00:22:30.263 --> 00:22:34.274
We're going to have to put you on blood thinners.

00:22:34.274 --> 00:22:41.360
" They're going to do all this stuff because you get these bad reports, but what's the first thing?

00:22:41.360 --> 00:22:44.171
"Well, I guess I'm dying.

00:22:44.171 --> 00:22:48.133
My marriage is going to heck.

00:22:48.133 --> 00:22:50.744
My kids are going to hell.

00:22:50.744 --> 00:22:52.933
My finances aren't doing any good.

00:23:00.080 --> 00:23:10.113
" You speak all those things out of your mouth, and the more you speak them, you'll have them.

00:23:10.113 --> 00:23:19.920
Most people go, "I don't believe that," but the devil knows the power of your tongue and its influence.

00:23:19.920 --> 00:23:26.144
Even when it comes to God, we are made in His image.

00:23:28.680 --> 00:23:30.229
As He is, so are we in this world.

00:23:30.229 --> 00:23:35.120
He spoke it, and it was.

00:23:35.120 --> 00:23:41.031
Remember what I told you: God's words do not return to Him void.

00:23:47.393 --> 00:23:47.679
They will accomplish that for which He sent them.

00:23:47.679 --> 00:24:00.400
When I went to the throne room and the Lord was speaking, none of His words died.

00:24:00.400 --> 00:24:03.320
They all became seeds before the throne.

00:24:21.227 --> 00:24:21.520
As they went together and all the letters came together, they formed sentences right before my face.

00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:27.360
They became a mustard seed in front of my face.

00:24:27.360 --> 00:24:33.850
All His words came out of Him and formed a mustard seed that started to grow because they didn't die.

00:24:33.850 --> 00:24:37.600
Everything the Lord says never returns to Him void.

00:24:37.600 --> 00:24:46.960
He does not speak to hear Himself talk; He speaks to make real things happen in a real world.

00:24:46.960 --> 00:24:51.520
